WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.400 --> 00:00:07.610
I'm so scared.

2
00:00:07.610 --> 00:00:08.870
Open the door!

3
00:00:08.870 --> 00:00:10.380
- I'm scared. - Don't be scared!

4
00:00:11.210 --> 00:00:13.950
Aji 3, we'll protect you.

5
00:00:20.221 --> 00:00:22.620
Don't open the door! Stay inside!

6
00:00:30.800 --> 00:00:32.560
- Hands up! - Hands in the air!

7
00:00:34.670 --> 00:00:36.130
Take them!

8
00:00:39.501 --> 00:00:40.541
Put your hands behind your back.

9
00:00:48.181 --> 00:00:49.380
(Santa Maria Research, Daeyang Shipbuilding)

10
00:00:59.461 --> 00:01:01.291
Aji 3, are you okay?

11
00:01:02.461 --> 00:01:03.660
Let's go home.

12
00:01:09.530 --> 00:01:10.801
Search the place thoroughly.

13
00:01:10.801 --> 00:01:12.901
- Yes, sir. - Search the stairs too.

14
00:01:13.610 --> 00:01:16.271
Search the stairs, and block the hallway.

15
00:01:17.480 --> 00:01:18.911
- Keep searching. - Yes, sir.

16
00:01:22.181 --> 00:01:23.250
Uncle.

17
00:01:24.580 --> 00:01:26.080
Do you think...

18
00:01:27.620 --> 00:01:29.351
Aji 3 will remember me?

19
00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:33.730
She's a robot, so she'll remember you forever.

20
00:01:35.691 --> 00:01:38.261
I'm happy.

21
00:01:49.310 --> 00:01:51.441
We should get new shoes for you, Aji 3.

22
00:01:52.480 --> 00:01:54.450
I met a lot of people.

23
00:01:55.551 --> 00:01:58.051
I want to read the emotions of many more people.

24
00:01:58.220 --> 00:02:00.851
She must've enjoyed the outside world she's seen for the first time.

25
00:02:01.791 --> 00:02:04.060
Aji 3, keep a backup of today's file.

26
00:02:04.491 --> 00:02:06.060
Backup is complete.

27
00:02:06.590 --> 00:02:09.661
Aji 3, are you happy to be back home?

28
00:02:09.661 --> 00:02:11.131
I need to be charged.

29
00:02:11.730 --> 00:02:13.871
Yes. Let's take some rest.

30
00:02:13.871 --> 00:02:16.101
We should take some rest too.

31
00:02:16.900 --> 00:02:19.270
I've completely burned myself out.

32
00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:20.811
Doctor Hong.

33
00:02:21.441 --> 00:02:23.710
We should still run a test and check if she's fine.

34
00:02:24.511 --> 00:02:25.511
Aji 3.

35
00:02:26.240 --> 00:02:29.011
What's the safest seat on a trip to Busan?

36
00:02:29.281 --> 00:02:30.321
- Seat Ma Dong Seok. - Seat Ma Dong Seok.

37
00:02:32.821 --> 00:02:35.351
Everything's perfect. I feel so accomplished.

38
00:02:57.841 --> 00:02:59.140
What are you thinking about?

39
00:03:00.680 --> 00:03:01.980
It's a secret.

40
00:03:04.221 --> 00:03:05.980
Hey, are you serious?

41
00:03:09.121 --> 00:03:10.191
I'm just happy.

42
00:03:10.960 --> 00:03:11.960
Why?

43
00:03:12.960 --> 00:03:14.031
I'm just happy...

44
00:03:15.230 --> 00:03:17.700
with everything that's going on right now.

45
00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:23.670
I achieved my goal for today,

46
00:03:24.700 --> 00:03:25.700
and...

47
00:03:26.240 --> 00:03:28.811
you're beside me right now.

48
00:03:32.511 --> 00:03:33.650
And...

49
00:03:36.580 --> 00:03:38.980
I can lie down and look at you like this.

50
00:03:39.221 --> 00:03:41.091
Hey, you're heavy.

51
00:03:41.091 --> 00:03:42.920
Well, just bear with it.

52
00:03:45.121 --> 00:03:46.221
By the way,

53
00:03:47.031 --> 00:03:48.490
you're a really good driver.

54
00:03:48.791 --> 00:03:52.700
See? I told you. I told you that you should be honored.

55
00:03:53.770 --> 00:03:55.871
Tell me if you need anything else.

56
00:03:56.971 --> 00:03:58.441
Do whatever you want.

57
00:03:59.270 --> 00:04:00.610
Make what you want to make.

58
00:04:00.610 --> 00:04:03.371
Instead, I want to be the first one to see it.

59
00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:11.150
You're still not safe to go outside by yourself, so I'll...

60
00:04:12.650 --> 00:04:13.751
Stop right there.

61
00:04:21.731 --> 00:04:23.191
- I need to go now. - What?

62
00:04:23.861 --> 00:04:25.160
You can spend time with her.

63
00:04:26.530 --> 00:04:28.931
- Where are you going to go? - I need to go home.

64
00:04:29.431 --> 00:04:30.540
Why can't you stay here?

65
00:04:30.900 --> 00:04:32.700
This is your place.

66
00:04:33.200 --> 00:04:34.710
Can't it be your place as well?

67
00:04:34.710 --> 00:04:36.111
What are you talking about?

68
00:04:39.140 --> 00:04:41.981
I'm hungry. Cook for me.

69
00:04:42.181 --> 00:04:43.650
Cook your own food.

70
00:04:43.650 --> 00:04:45.921
Come on. I have no energy.

71
00:04:47.191 --> 00:04:49.150
Come on. Cook for me.

72
00:04:50.090 --> 00:04:51.460
Make me something.

73
00:04:51.921 --> 00:04:53.520
Go and cook something yourself.

74
00:04:54.691 --> 00:04:55.731
Come on. I want food.

75
00:04:55.731 --> 00:04:58.030
- Okay, okay. Get up. - Okay.

76
00:05:06.671 --> 00:05:09.270
Back when I was young, I went on a field trip.

77
00:05:09.710 --> 00:05:12.981
But there was no one to make gimbap for me, so I had to make my own.

78
00:05:14.350 --> 00:05:17.481
My aunt went on a field trip for the first time when she was my age.

79
00:05:18.220 --> 00:05:20.520
But she didn't know how to make gimbap.

80
00:05:20.751 --> 00:05:23.960
So she made rice balls instead.

81
00:05:23.960 --> 00:05:25.790
That was the first time she ever made these.

82
00:05:27.590 --> 00:05:29.431
Why would a kid have to make her own gimbap?

83
00:05:31.030 --> 00:05:33.431
Because there was no one there to make them for her.

84
00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:35.400
Your aunt...

85
00:05:36.171 --> 00:05:39.501
must've gotten teased by her friends on that field trip.

86
00:05:39.671 --> 00:05:41.770
Apparently, no one ate with her.

87
00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:44.241
But my mom did.

88
00:05:44.640 --> 00:05:47.481
That's why my aunt became a guardian angel for my mom.

89
00:05:51.450 --> 00:05:52.621
Here. Try it.

90
00:05:56.450 --> 00:05:57.460
Why are you laughing?

91
00:05:58.421 --> 00:05:59.460
It's a secret.

92
00:05:59.460 --> 00:06:02.231
Why is it a secret? Then I'm not going to give you this.

93
00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:03.561
I just found out...

94
00:06:04.830 --> 00:06:07.270
who my guardian angel was.

95
00:06:08.571 --> 00:06:09.631
Who was it?

96
00:06:59.551 --> 00:07:02.421
You told Yoo Cheol everything?

97
00:07:04.321 --> 00:07:05.421
I guess he was...

98
00:07:06.191 --> 00:07:07.561
bound to find out sooner or later.

99
00:07:10.400 --> 00:07:11.801
You didn't tell him about the other stuff, did you?

100
00:07:12.001 --> 00:07:14.400
No, I didn't tell him.

101
00:07:14.700 --> 00:07:16.801
Martin already got away.

102
00:07:17.501 --> 00:07:19.840
I just need to get the charges dropped.

103
00:07:21.210 --> 00:07:22.811
Make sure to get Director Ye.

104
00:07:23.681 --> 00:07:24.741
Go back.

105
00:07:25.241 --> 00:07:27.611
I will not become in-laws with a criminal.

106
00:07:32.020 --> 00:07:34.491
This is a gift from Chairman Hwang.

107
00:07:42.061 --> 00:07:46.631
The shares in his borrowed name accounts were transferred to Ri El.

108
00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:48.371
Chairman Hwang...

109
00:07:49.030 --> 00:07:51.840
wants you to become the new director.

110
00:07:52.270 --> 00:07:53.941
If you accept,

111
00:07:53.941 --> 00:07:56.171
he will support you wholeheartedly.

112
00:07:57.611 --> 00:08:01.350
He wants me to become director and cover up all his shortcomings?

113
00:08:01.350 --> 00:08:04.981
That would make it easier for you to do your duties...

114
00:08:04.981 --> 00:08:06.821
once you become a director.

115
00:08:06.991 --> 00:08:09.850
You just have to oust Director Kim.

116
00:08:09.850 --> 00:08:11.890
Ousting him isn't enough.

117
00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:14.330
He will come back.

118
00:08:16.731 --> 00:08:19.301
We must make sure he loses the will to come back.

119
00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:23.231
Will you use his illness?

120
00:08:34.180 --> 00:08:35.280
Hold on.

121
00:08:45.361 --> 00:08:47.231
I know what you're thinking.

122
00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:51.201
But one's misfortune sometimes becomes...

123
00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:53.231
another person's opportunity.

124
00:08:53.601 --> 00:08:57.670
What you need at a time like that is the courage to go with it.

125
00:09:02.741 --> 00:09:03.841
How...

126
00:09:07.511 --> 00:09:09.251
How is that courage?

127
00:09:09.251 --> 00:09:12.621
It's courage. Not anyone can do it.

128
00:09:14.050 --> 00:09:15.951
You can't say that, Dad.

129
00:09:16.721 --> 00:09:18.621
It doesn't make sense.

130
00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:21.831
I'm your daughter.

131
00:09:23.660 --> 00:09:25.900
Do you think I'll be happy?

132
00:09:25.900 --> 00:09:27.701
Everything passes.

133
00:09:28.400 --> 00:09:31.140
When it does, you'll see it was nothing.

134
00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:42.011
Your father looked over his crime,

135
00:09:42.011 --> 00:09:43.650
in return for the rebate.

136
00:09:44.050 --> 00:09:45.081
Okay.

137
00:09:47.591 --> 00:09:51.491
He didn't kill anyone.

138
00:09:58.501 --> 00:09:59.501
Hi.

139
00:09:59.501 --> 00:10:02.371
Does Min Kyu have an illness?

140
00:10:03.131 --> 00:10:05.001
I think your dad and mine...

141
00:10:05.300 --> 00:10:08.211
will use that to do something terrible.

142
00:10:09.070 --> 00:10:10.640
- What? - I called thinking...

143
00:10:10.640 --> 00:10:12.410
you wouldn't know about this.

144
00:10:14.111 --> 00:10:15.810
You don't know about it, do you?

145
00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:18.881
No, I...

146
00:10:20.351 --> 00:10:21.951
I'll call you right back.

147
00:10:44.611 --> 00:10:48.351
(Chairman Hwang Do Won)

