00:13:08.351 --> 00:13:10.761
Would you mind if I join in?

161
00:13:11.091 --> 00:13:13.861
I'm right here. Respect my existence.

162
00:13:14.131 --> 00:13:17.201
Do you want me to buy you a pair of Heart Balls?

163
00:13:17.300 --> 00:13:19.400
I shouldn't have fallen asleep then.

164
00:13:19.400 --> 00:13:21.201
I didn't know this would happen.

165
00:13:21.871 --> 00:13:23.001
The Lover.

166
00:13:24.300 --> 00:13:25.570
I feel lonely.

167
00:13:26.170 --> 00:13:29.910
I feel lonely now. So lonely.

168
00:13:31.711 --> 00:13:33.140
Goodness.

169
00:13:33.611 --> 00:13:35.611
I told you she'd be pretty.

170
00:13:36.280 --> 00:13:38.520
Who is she? Do you know her?

171
00:13:40.121 --> 00:13:43.790
Your hair, your style. Wow.

172
00:13:43.790 --> 00:13:45.091
You know her too?

173
00:13:45.890 --> 00:13:46.890
Hello.

174
00:13:48.190 --> 00:13:50.631
People die if they make a drastic change.

175
00:13:51.461 --> 00:13:52.530
(Vegetable juice)

176
00:13:52.530 --> 00:13:54.231
Drink these and wake up.

177
00:13:54.231 --> 00:13:57.400
The style changed but not the character. Good.

178
00:13:57.400 --> 00:14:00.371
I'm in a bad mood. Shall I dye my hair ash blue?

179
00:14:00.371 --> 00:14:02.810
Do it. It's not bad.

180
00:14:02.810 --> 00:14:04.981
Hoktal, what do you say? Do you want to do it with me?

181
00:14:08.780 --> 00:14:11.020
I'm not the hair dye type.

182
00:14:11.020 --> 00:14:13.851
Up until yesterday, you'd do anything I asked.

183
00:14:13.851 --> 00:14:15.790
Why the sudden change?

184
00:14:15.951 --> 00:14:18.160
Did Sun Hye tell you not to do it?

185
00:14:18.160 --> 00:14:21.290
She shrugged. That's despicable.

186
00:14:22.430 --> 00:14:23.660
- Hoktal. - Yes?

187
00:14:24.101 --> 00:14:27.070
Go back to the time when you were nice to me.

188
00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:29.930
I feel so lonely on days like this.

189
00:14:29.930 --> 00:14:31.400
Why? Is today a special day?

190
00:14:32.001 --> 00:14:34.940
No, it's just...

191
00:14:35.741 --> 00:14:37.410
Fine, don't do anything.

192
00:14:37.410 --> 00:14:39.310
I'll just get angry if you do something.

193
00:14:42.550 --> 00:14:43.780
Don't do anything.

194
00:14:43.780 --> 00:14:45.751
- Hello. - Hi.

195
00:14:46.420 --> 00:14:48.121
- You bought juice. - Yes.

196
00:14:52.261 --> 00:14:55.491
- Gosh, it's good. - Yes.

197
00:14:55.930 --> 00:14:57.701
Something needs fixing.

198
00:14:57.701 --> 00:14:59.601
Okay.

199
00:15:02.930 --> 00:15:04.940
What? Is your scalp itchy?

200
00:15:04.940 --> 00:15:06.101
No, no.

201
00:15:08.270 --> 00:15:09.810
You're made for each other.

202
00:15:11.241 --> 00:15:13.810
Ssanip, I need you to go to Yongsan.

203
00:15:13.810 --> 00:15:15.381
What? Where?

204
00:15:15.381 --> 00:15:18.520
Buy these, and come straight to the outhouse.

205
00:15:19.481 --> 00:15:22.451
Oh, parts, Yongsan? Okay, Doctor.

206
00:15:23.251 --> 00:15:24.420
See you.

207
00:15:25.690 --> 00:15:28.331
- Take your time. - I love you.

208
00:15:28.331 --> 00:15:30.131
- Me too. - Bye.

209
00:15:36.940 --> 00:15:38.101
Pai, by the way,

210
00:15:39.341 --> 00:15:42.841
you look a bit... Strange.

211
00:15:43.111 --> 00:15:44.140
How so?

212
00:15:44.140 --> 00:15:46.780
You don't look like you used to.

213
00:15:46.780 --> 00:15:48.351
The difference is...

214
00:15:49.150 --> 00:15:52.251
Oh, your eyes are bigger.

215
00:15:52.251 --> 00:15:54.251
I'm not wearing glasses.

216
00:15:54.751 --> 00:15:55.851
I see.

217
00:15:58.690 --> 00:16:00.690
Your forehead's wider too.

218
00:16:01.331 --> 00:16:03.160
I parted my bangs.

219
00:16:04.430 --> 00:16:05.501
I see.

220
00:16:09.231 --> 00:16:11.341
You parted your bangs.

221
00:16:12.101 --> 00:16:15.540
Wait, your hair. Wasn't your hair curly?

222
00:16:15.841 --> 00:16:17.640
I got sick of it, so I straightened it.

223
00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:23.111
Does my hair look weird?

224
00:16:23.381 --> 00:16:24.420
No.

225
00:16:25.221 --> 00:16:26.351
It doesn't.

226
00:16:29.751 --> 00:16:30.820
Let's go.

227
00:16:35.131 --> 00:16:36.761
It doesn't look weird.

228
00:16:39.001 --> 00:16:40.871
Even without Ji A next to me,

229
00:16:40.871 --> 00:16:42.831
I keep practicing going out on my own.

230
00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:46.741
Right. I guess she can't be around you all the time.

231
00:16:46.741 --> 00:16:48.241
She's no longer a robot.

232
00:16:48.471 --> 00:16:49.670
Exactly.

233
00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:52.910
I liked that about her when she was a robot.

234
00:16:53.981 --> 00:16:55.180
Aren't you afraid?

235
00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:59.020
I keep telling myself that she's next to me,

236
00:16:59.020 --> 00:17:02.121
and that seems to help a bit.

237
00:17:02.491 --> 00:17:04.860
Your index seems to be okay right now.

238
00:17:04.860 --> 00:17:07.090
As long as you avoid a situation...

239
00:17:07.090 --> 00:17:09.130
where you suddenly face a crowd,

240
00:17:09.130 --> 00:17:12.030
don't you think you can handle everyday life?

241
00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:14.671
Would that ever happen?

242
00:17:15.570 --> 00:17:17.540
Take care. Goodbye.

243
